            "headline": "Netflix to surpass YouTube in video revenue by 2025 according to Omdia, with Netflix projecting $46.2B and YouTube at $45.6B.",
            "id": "d86ab545-c363-407f-a52b-e09a8578f13e",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Business Wire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "In 2025, Netflix is projected to surpass YouTube for the first time in total video revenue. Exclusive Omdia research revealed at MIP TV London 2025 indicates that in 2024, YouTube led the market with $42.5 billion in revenue, while Netflix earned $39.2 billion. However, forecasts for 2025 show Netflix taking the lead with $46.2 billion, with $43.2 billion coming from subscriptions and $3.2 billion from advertising. Meanwhile, YouTube is expected to generate $45.6 billion in revenue.",
