            "id": "bc5ae96b-5e66-4ee7-91d0-f1c502a53298",
            "is_major": true,
            "source": "GlobeNewswire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "A construction contract has been signed between Tariston AS, a group company of AS Nordecon, and O\u00dc Rail Baltic Estonia for the initial phase of railway infrastructure construction on the Rail Baltica main route in P\u00e4rnu County. This phase will focus on the Selja-Tootsi section, encompassing the construction of 14.5 kilometers of railway embankment and six structures, including three ecoducts, two viaducts, and a pedestrian and bicycle tunnel. The project will involve moving approximately 2.5 million cubic meters of earth in total. The contract is valued at 62.3 million euros, plus VAT, with a completion deadline set for the conclusion of 2028.",
